{"text": "I don't normally root for billionaires, especially in reality. In this case, I'll make an exception. In summary: Heavily armed billionaire philanthropist vigilante visits a maximum security psycho ward and beats the living â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ out of its patients. Neutral:- A bit linear in the opening/tutorial segments, but you'll be having a blast once it opens up Pros:- â€¢ Sprawling, metroidvania style world, with multiple branching and interconnected pathways, along with cunning ways of getting around undetected such as grappling hooks and ziplines â€¢ Endless means at your disposal with which to take out goons - live out your wildest Navy Seal copypasta fantasies (\" \")  â€¢ Use darkness, ventilation ducts, gargoyles, and other high-up vantage points to execute stealth takedowns â€¢ The FreeFlow combat system is engrossing, engaging, and actively encourages you chain together bigger and bigger combos â€¢ An abundance of lateral thinking riddles and forced perspective puzzles to crack â€¢ An abundance of hidden objects and trophies to collect, which unlocks extra game modes at no extra cost â€¢ X-ray vision allows you to see through thin walls, see breadcrumb trails of evidence, and also help plan your assault on a group armed thugs in advance â€¢ Solid variety of goons - you are challenged to rethink the way you play each time a new one is introduced â€¢ Never gets stale, you'll be coming back to play this more than once â€¢ Incredible attention to detail and world building â€¢ Each 'dungeon' has something new to offer â€¢ Campaign mode is just the right length â€¢ Appeals to all skill levels â€¢ Has aged like a fine wine â€¢ Excellent pacing Cons:- â€¢ Sometimes, countering/parrying/riposting doesn't register, and can be frustrating â€¢ Some riddles can be a little obscure Overall:- 9/10, absolutely the most fun you can have in a Batman themed video game If Comic Book worlds, superheroes, and supervillains don't hold your attention, seriously don't overlook this one - give it a shot.", "appid": "35140", "steamid": "profiles/76561197997808191", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602676800.0}
