{"text": "Northgard is like a simple version of Tropico but with a Viking theme. I am personally a huge fan of resource management/building games so thoroughly enjoyed it--- particularly the campaign, which has a very engaging story. I also really appreciated that the voice-overs tried to pronounce the Nordic terms and names in a more authentic manner rather than butchering them with an American accent (a very small detail but sometimes these small details matter!)  The building mechanisms are not that complex so it's very easy to learn (although I'm sure that hard-core simulation fans would probably want more variety of buildings). After 30 hours of play, the strategies get somewhat repetitive, but I have only played single player-- and almost 50 hours at that so I feel like my money was really well spent. I'm sure multiplayer brings a whole new set of interesting game dynamics.", "appid": "466560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198014625189", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1528804800.0}
