{"text": "â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€âšªâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€  |â—€â €â €â–Žâ €â–Žâ €â €â–¶|â €ðŸ”Šâ €1:48 / 2:20 â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â € âœ±â €â–£â €â–­â €âŒœâŒŸ This review is a combination of my almost two thousand hours on PSO2 before Steam, as well the hours I am currently undergoing on Steam. Before hand, my history with PSO2 is simple. I have waited almost a decade for this amazing MMORPG to make its way to the West and I want to share all of its amazing aspects and its negative ones with you!  So please, have a seat, make yourself at home, grab a bite to eat and a drink as well. And I hope you enjoy my review of Phantasy Star Online 2. â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ Phantasy Star Online 2 is an MMORPG made in Japan. It is said by many to be the Japanese World of Warcraft. This game was made and developed by Sega back around 2012 as a Japanese only title. It was not long till word got out about the interesting take on the MMORPG genre and people across the world wanted a feel for Phantasy Star Online 2. That being said, the game would see three major instances where it was planned to move West. Two of these failed and mostly where adverts saying it was coming over. The third major event under this \"move\" west idea. Was the end of last year, and all this year so far. Phantasy Star Online 2, will and would come to the west and shortly after have its well deserved global release. Allowing everyone to partake in this Japanese master piece.  With all of this being said, the release of Phantasy Star Online 2 in the West is an amazing thing. It allows us to experience a game that has interesting ideas of gameplay, new ideas in story telling, and a wonderful aspect that; personally, I never thought possible.  â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ So, Phantasy Star Online 2. It is on the surface a run of the mill MMORPG. You select a class, make a character, level them up, play PVE and (Just added with Episode 4) PVP, and reach end game content. Doing raids and joining guilds/alliances (As in PSO2). But when playing Phantasy Star Online 2. It becomes really clear that this game feels different. Firstly the game has a full blown single player campaign with full CG cutscenes, as well full English and Japanese voice acting. (Language can be changed at the main menu) This alone appeals to people like myself. Who do love single player games and love doing solo stuff on MMORPGs. This single player experience is fairly long and can take well over 24 hours of play time to complete if you do not skip cutscenes and dialogs.  Taking into account it is an MMORPG. And most people will want to experience something nice and fun on the MMO aspect of things. Well firstly, this game has everything you want from a S rank MMO. It has the aspect of crafting, grinding, raids, tons and tons of quests, and loads of events and massive raids that are throughout the day. These are called; UQs or Urgent Quests. Each time being different than the last, with some repeats here and there. These can range from basic raid style quests where you and a ton of people start at one end and get from point A to point B. Others are a tower defense mission, and AOT style mission, and a quest to go into a local area and kill a select number of mobs to reach a point limit.  Now, Phantasy Star Online 2 does have loads to do. No matter who you are or where you came from. PSO2 has what you need. If you love single player games and solo questing. You have a episodic single player campaign, and if you are a fan of the more classic side of the MMORPG genre. PSO2 has plenty to do. Around over two hundred hours worth of basic content on the MMO aspect alone. Over twenty-four hours on the single player side of things. And thousands of hours on the social end of the game.  YES, thousands. Why? Simple. Phantasy Star Online 2 is the most social MMORPG to date. The community does so much lobby grind it's not even funny. Most people will find themselves spending hours just chatting in the Cafe, Gate Area, or Shopping District. And if not at one of these three. You can find people hanging in their Personal Quarters or Alliance Quarters. No matter what it is you are wanting from a game. Phantasy Star Online 2 100% has it all for you.  â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ The game feels wonderful, well balanced and well thought-out. The game now has PVP and what I know, it does not matter on what gear you have or your level. It matters about knowing how to use that gear that counts. The game outside of PVP feels smooth and crisp. The game plays amazing and looks real good for its age. This means that fellow nerds and gamers alike can easily pick up PSO2 and play with no issues at all.  â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ The story is kinda odd to take in. So in PSO2 you are playing as someone playing an VRMMORPG. And the story is actually well written and well done. I won't share much about it aside from, please give it a shot. You will not regret it. But no spoils here! â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ So the game does have some issues. And tho I love this game a lot. These issues do need to be pointed out.  1. The economy in the game, as far as cosmetics and fashion. Is completely trash. Everything is over priced and can take a none premium member weeks to get an outfit set sometimes.  2. The game is heavy on the social aspect, and with people. There is DRAMA, and at times. Lots of it. 3. The grind for levels can take a long time to reach at times. You really have to work hard for it.   4. There is an issue with Steam versions not showing all the products on the player shop. So if you see something on another character you want and look up that item and not find it. Please ask someone that is not a Steam user to assist in finding that said item. 5. The game does have an issue with episodes taking a while to release in the West. That means, when you done all you can. You only can really sit around and socialize with other players till the next episode. So if you like that, no issues. But if you don't then there is an issue atm with content release times.  â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ Phantasy Star Online 2 is an amazing game that I know many will love, loads will like, and some will hate. And tho the game has some issues as stated above. The overall game is wonderful and I highly encourage people to pick PSO2 up and give her a shot. It is free after all so in the end if you say, \"Huh, not my cup of tea.* You don't lose much, just a little bit of your time. â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬â–¬ Overall, this game is wonderful. I love every second I spend in PSO2 and I know you will too! This game gets a high 9.5/10, with a ð“›ð“²ð“µð“µð”‚ seal of approval! If you are a new player and want to join a noob friendly Alliance that not only helps out each other, but is also highly active. Then Ashen Saints is the Alliance for you! We are located on Ship 1 and mostly hang on Block 5. If you wish to join us. DM me on Steam or come say hi in the Cafe over on Block 5.", "appid": "1056640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003160902", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596888000.0}
