{"text": "Another game that falls under the 'Amazing concept but terrible execution' category. It is an open world, gear based PvP Third Person Shooter between two factions, Criminals and Enforcers.  Before I begin with my review, let me quickly add that I played the game almost 7 years ago on my older account, so my current playtime doesn't represent my total playtime.  This game is a really tragic mess which could be a top tier game (especially for a F2P one) if it weren't for a lot of terrible balancing decisions and gimmicks, which I can only describe as \"Developers thought something was cool so they added it without any second thoughts\", - but more to that in the con/negative section of the review. For now, let me start with the Good this game has.     There is a lot to criticize about the game but the customization is definitely not one of those things. The game has probably the best car and character customization in any game. - Seriously, you can design your character whatever way you want by slapping symbols on your face, body and clothes and can turn a boring white sweater into a piece of art. The options are limitless and the only thing preventing you from designing your character the way you want is your own creativity and its range. It is definitely the best part of the game and people who are into that stuff will spend a lot of time in the design creator to make your own symbols.    APB Reloaded is an open world game with PvP missions, there are two huge big city maps and they are populated by civilian NPCs or chaos wrecking players. The way it works is basically you roam in a city until you match make into a mission, which happens in the same city with no loading screen, no teleporting, nothing. - You just find yourself a car if you haven't yet and drive to your destination. However what is really neat is the fact you can do little things in the open world outside of missions, such as mugging civilian NPCs as a criminal or loot stores OR bust criminals that do said actions as an Enforcer.  This is unfortunately really all the positives I have to say about the game, I could be sitting here for ten minutes and think what else I could add, but I really can't.  Missions are really a hit or miss, sometimes you get a fun one where one group has to spray grafity and the other has to prevent that and the missions final stage is a full blown Team Death Match... And sometimes it's literally chasing cars non stop. Some of the objectives are just absolutely terrible, they are terribly placed on the map and have the most boring PvP imaginable, for example there's one objective where one group needs to steal cars and deliver them to an area, and the issue is that cars in missions  are incredible fast and stupidly durable (unless you have an RPG) and all you need to do is drive into a massive circle for a split second and the objective is done. These missions just result in shooting a tank constantly with your terrible starter pea shooter, or just losing the objective all together. There's another final stage objective, where both teams need to get an armored vehicle and own it until you've reached a score, so - yet another car chase and shoot until the car finally blows up! (or doesn't.). And when the objective vehicle does blow up, you need to drive to a spot to steal the same vehicle again and do it all over. These missions COULD be fun, if it weren't for the problem the wheels of vehicles are invincible and the fact every car in America allegedly has bullet proof windows, so the only way to kill the driver is blow up the vehicle. Overall just a very boring and frustrating experience. New players have to prepare for a lot of abuse in the early stage of the game, considering this game is practically dead, new players are forced more than often to face veteran players, who have much better weapons, character mods and weapon mods. The weapons you are given at start are either absolutely terrible and are only good with weapon mods, or are just an unsatisfying mess hard to use. Basically, prepare to fight people with RPGs and fully Modded M16s while you're stuck with a weapon that has much worse recoil, has a terrible DPS and RPM. While the maps are pretty to look at, they can be an absolute mess in missions. They range from fighting in some back alley, giving the health department a heart attack at the lack of social distance, or you're forced to steal a car in an open parking lot - surrounded by a ton of roofs you can climb on and a massive high way you can snipe from. Rarely there was an in between. I seriously don't understand who thought of that, who thought that fighting ontop of rooftops which you can only reach with ladders that force you into an animation and leaves you very vulnerable was a fun thing. Or who thought that making an objective stand out in the open while the enemy can just sit on a high way with sniper rifles and kill you before you can even see the objective was fun? Unbalanced mess. Think that's enough.  The Gameplay is an absolute mess, just as you'd expect from a grind game where veterans have God tier weapons while new players and average players don't. There are so many decisions made that make you grab your head and simply go '... What?'. Let me start by mentioning that there's no headshot multiplier, - yep. No headshot multipliers, that means you can easily stay behind a dumpster and head glitch with no penalty or risk involved. (For those who don't know what headglitch is, it's a term for standing behind cover where only your head is visible to the enemy but you can still shoot. Headglitches are fine in games like CS, where headshot multipliers exist, but not in a game like this one). It's even worse if you combine it with the fact you can crouch spam constantly, and now combine it with a sniper on a bridge half a mile away. Doesn't sound like fun, does it? Then there's also the issue that this game has health regeneration, so unless it's a cqc combat, expect enemies to tank five shots, go to cover and sit there for five seconds to heal up again - and it's especially frustrating for sniper and DMR players considering they can't one hit people AT ALL. Sniper duels are the most frustrating things in the game, and are on certain missions mandatory because of the map.. But now, let me get to my biggest complaint - CARS. They are just total cheese because you just quickly climb into one and suddenly are invincible. Cars with bullet proof Windows are no fun, especially if you didn't grind to get rocket launchers (which require a lot of explosion and grenade kills, if I am correct.). I've had an enemy VIP constantly jump in and out of his car constantly to headglitch and shoot me while I was trying to destroy his car or run after him. I have a feeling if it weren't for cars being tanky and making the player invincible, or RPGs being hard to obtain, this game would be much more enjoyable.   I probably don't have to go too much into detail what happens if a game allows you to play as female characters and customize them fully in depth, it what happens of you allow people in an F2P game to make their own designs and symbols, do I? Basically, a lot of half nude anime girls running with guns with swastika vans. Overall, the game really is not worth the time nor effort at the current state it is in right now, it is a dead game with less than a thousand players, it's unbalanced, very unfriendly towards new players and is just a frustrating experience in general. However there's still hope, apparently the game is getting an updated engine and the Devs are adding, removing and Re balancing a lot of stuff which the veteran players are allegedly praising.. But for now, it's a 5/10 at best.", "appid": "113400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198017978266", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594123200.0}
