{"text": "I didn't like this game. I'm not saying it's bad. Actually I really like the idea behind this game. But 14 levels in I quit the game and left it minimized to get all cards. The gameplay was just so frustrating to me that I just couldn't go on. I just couldn't stand the helplessness of the movement system. Losing momentum and not being able to do something about it(apart from just restarting the level) simply rubbed me the wrong way. I know that it's a completely subjective thing and thus this review is pointless, but I just needed to put this out here.", "appid": "290280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198309272931", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1493899200.0}
{"text": "first grabbed my attention with its steampunk style which I utterly love, however, the next thing I noticed was all the negative reviews. I took a moment to glance through them and thought: â€œit canâ€™t be that bad. Iâ€™m sure people are just being overdramaticâ€ and it was also on sale. Oh was I so wrong!   Starting up the game, youâ€™re asked information on how youâ€™d like to view the adult content throughout: all, none, light, etc. Pick your option and away you go.    Stepping into the shoes of one Tirs something-or-other you are instantly made into a crappy boyfriend who constantly makes his long-term other-half second to his desires and future career. Needless to say, Tirs isnâ€™t the nicest person in the world but heâ€™s a genius so who cares, right? Well, obviously his boyfriend did as he dumps Tirsâ€™ sorry arse. This leads our MC to throw himself further into his career goals, leading him directly into the lap of one, professor Marc...  into his lap. Now, hereâ€™s where things get really interesting plot wise; Early on in the game, Marc propositions Tirs to see if he wants to â€œblow off some steamâ€ casually. You can completely refuse â€“ but doing so leads you steadily to a bad ending only! In other words, it may be consensual between the two men but as the player, you are forced into this act if you have any plans of reaching an ending with any of the three LIâ€™s.   This forced   happens again further down the line. If you want to get off of Marcâ€™s route and onto one of the none psychos routes, you have to once again, agree to shag Marc but this time, as a threesome. I can very much see why this â€¦ â€œinterestingâ€ idea by the devs had caused a lot of backlash.    The whole plot of this game isnâ€™t much better. It is hugely ambition but aims higher than it can deliver. Heavy topics such as blackmail, threats, accidental murder and kidnapping â€“ just to name a few â€“ are bland and lacking any real emotion. Example, the murder thing; thereâ€™s a single statement that he feels bad about it but no other mention until the end of a good route which, once again, itâ€™s a measly line or two. Thereâ€™s just no impact! The sheer amount of grammatical errors do nothing to help the situation either!     The description clearly states â€œKey scenes have voice acting!â€ but it feels rather random. If I were to hazard a guess, Iâ€™d say that the voice actors were given their lines but with no instructions other than that. â€œTirsâ€ the MC is sometimes called â€œTearsâ€ and other times as â€œTursâ€. At the very least, have everyone know how to say the damn guy's name!   As for the art, as stated before, I am a lover of the steampunk style and it is what original drew me in but even this was ruined. A select few characters just look weird while on screen together. Iâ€™m no artist but itâ€™s like the LIâ€™s were given the most attention while the supporting characters werenâ€™t given as much detail. The CGâ€™s are very well done but the contrast between the sprites and CGâ€™s are huge! Characters no longer look like themselves and itâ€™s more as if you are seeing an older sibling or some such. Personally, it really threw me off.   Overall, I really wouldnâ€™t recommend this to anyone, even if it were on sale. Seriously â€“ a â€œgeniusâ€, top of his class guy that somehow manages to constantly get himself into astonishingly ridiculous situations makes me think heâ€™s clearly a moron and his class mates are completely brain dead. He is wholly self-centred, is angry when his best friend tries to reach out to him merely to check up on him and is far too obsessed with space to care about much else! Letâ€™s be real, this is an adult content game and even that is a let-down â€“ it just felt like a chore after so long. I am in no way in an extremely long, loveless marriage with this VN so I donâ€™t appreciate being made to feel like Iâ€™m just trying to push my way through our annual romp in a desperate and fruitless attempt to spark the fire of a long dead flame!   Hard pass really!     If Iâ€™m super honest here, I just want to be done with this so yeah, I havenâ€™t even proof-read my own review and I just donâ€™t care!", "appid": "763990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044949801", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597579200.0}
