{"text": "*Ahem* sorry... Material Girl is a hentai â€œadventureâ€ game made by Dieselmine, which feels more like a CG Collector game than a proper game. For starters thereâ€™s pretty much no plot. The whole game can be summed up as â€œSakura needs money to pay the bills, so she searches for part-time jobs and ends up getting abused in multiple ways by different peopleâ€. I can more or less forgive a game for having an excuse plot if thereâ€™s some sort of plot progression but this game even lacks that. Once you get past the 2 deadlines (which are very easy to do tbh) youâ€™re left to your own devices without anything to do aside from finding different ways to get Sakura corrupted (read: r4ped) and â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ her out once her lewdness meter is high enough. What makes it even worse is its terribad translation. Machine-translated games are notorious for having awkward dialogues that barely make any sense to anyone who knows the language it was translated to (let alone native speakers) but this one also has numerous typos, odd line breaks, and some naming inconsistencies to boot. To give you an idea of how bad it is I spent more time pressing the â€œskip dialogueâ€ key than reading it. The only thing that keeps this game away from being an absolute disaster is the art. Itâ€™s quite decent if you ask me, even though itâ€™s censored and there are a few CG that may look odd (how long is that foot fetishistâ€™s tongue btw?). They even animated a few of the scenes, which is an unexpected plus. In short, I canâ€™t recommend it. Material Girl could have been decent if the dev got someone competent to translate it, put more effort into the story instead of focusing only on the lewd scenes, and made it less rapey.", "appid": "644570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198137722104", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605355200.0}
